<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="TheWellnessGPT gives evidence-led wellness answers for life in Malaysia: clear comparisons, real mechanisms, and guidance relevant to local products, prices, and everyday life."
  path="/about/"
>
  <article class="article">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">About</p>
      <h1>Wellness, decoded for life in Malaysia.</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheWellnessGPT answers one question well: <em>what actually works for my health?</em> Most wellness content online is either vague, hyped, or quietly selling you something. We give clear, evidence-led answers, built for life in Malaysia and what you can actually buy here.</p>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mechanism and evidence first.</strong> We explain <em>why</em> something works (or doesn't), and how strong the evidence actually is, before we get to any product.</li>
          <li><strong>Real comparisons.</strong> We weigh the actual options you can buy in Malaysia, side by side, on the same terms.</li>
          <li><strong>Local reality.</strong> Prices in ringgit, where to buy (Shopee, Watsons, Guardian, pharmacies), and what fits a hot, busy, urban life.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
        <p>Our content is educational. For persistent or worsening symptoms, or before starting a new supplement, see a doctor or pharmacist.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
